# Generate and display correlation heatmap for numerical features

numeric_df = happy_df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number])

# Calculate the correlation matrix
cor = numeric_df.corr(method="pearson")

# Plot the heatmap
f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))
sns.heatmap(cor, mask=np.zeros_like(cor, dtype=bool),
            cmap="Blues", square=True, ax=ax)

In[257]:
# Create subplots
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(16, 6))
plt.tight_layout(pad=2)

# Plot for top 10 happiest countries
axes[0].set_title('Top 10 Happiest Countries Life Expectancy')
sns.barplot(x=top_10.country_name, y=top_10.healthy_life_expectancy, ax=axes[0])
axes[0].set_xlabel('Country Name')
axes[0].set_ylabel('Life Expectancy')
axes[0].set_xticks(range(len(top_10.country_name)))
axes[0].set_xticklabels(top_10.country_name, rotation=45, ha='right')

# Plot for bottom 10 least happy countries
axes[1].set_title('Bottom 10 Least Happy Countries Life Expectancy')
sns.barplot(x=bottom_10.country_name, y=bottom_10.healthy_life_expectancy, ax=axes[1])
axes[1].set_xlabel('Country Name')
axes[1].set_ylabel('Life Expectancy')
axes[1].set_xticks(range(len(bottom_10.country_name)))
axes[1].set_xticklabels(bottom_10.country_name, rotation=45, ha='right')

# Display the plot
plt.show()
